@ravipesala 
Done, please check agian. All the test cases and static check have passed.
For concurrent query scenario, if you mean multiple threads
if  thread1 and thread2 starts at the same time and ends at different time, and not streaming like process, we record the max of them.
If threre are many threads doing streaming like process, we only record the total time of this step.
but if you mean different users they load data concurrent, it is not support, because this PR is only used by the developer to estimate the load time.

Thank you!

LOAD DATA inpath 'D:/inputPath/carbonTest.csv' INTO TABLE carbonTest options( 'COLUMNDICT '='name:D:/Carbon/carbonData/name.csv,sex:D:/Carbon/carbonData/sex.csv'), 
user needs to set as "column_Name: column_Path", and multiple columns and file paths can be delimited by ",'.
